# Lumo Language Rules for Cursor

Lumo is an LLM-native language where EVERY operator is a plain English word. No symbols in program logic.

## Syntax Mapping ‚Äî Symbol to Word

| Traditional | Lumo | Example |
|------------|------|---------|
| `+` | `plus` | `x plus y` |
| `-` | `minus` | `x minus y` |
| `*` | `times` | `x times y` |
| `/` | `divby` | `x divby y` |
| `%` | `modulo` | `x modulo y` |
| `==` | `equals` | `x equals y` |
| `>` | `above` | `x above y` |
| `<` | `below` | `x below y` |
| `>=` | `atleast` | `x atleast y` |
| `<=` | `atmost` | `x atmost y` |
| `&&` | `and` | `a and b` |
| `\|\|` | `or` | `a or b` |
| `!` | `not` | `not a` |
| `= (assign)` | `let x be` / `set x be` | `let x be 5` / `set x be 6` |
| `{ }` | block...`end` | `if ... then ... end` |
| `fn/def` | `define ... taking` | `define add taking a, b` |
| `f(x)` | `call f passing x` | `call add passing 1, 2` |
| `arr[i]` | `get arr at i` | `get nums at 0` |

## Statement Forms

```lumo
intent "purpose"                              # REQUIRED first line
let name be expression                        # declare variable
set name be expression                        # mutate (must let first)
print expression                              # output
skip                                          # no-op
read name                                     # stdin input
return expression                             # function return
call name passing arg1, arg2                  # function call (statement)
put name at index be value                    # mutate element
```

## Block Forms

```lumo
# While loop
repeat while condition
  statements
end

# Count loop
repeat 10 times
  statements
end

# For-each loop
for each item in mylist
  statements
end

# Conditional
if condition then
  statements
elif condition then
  statements
else
  statements
end

# Function
define fname taking param1, param2
  statements
  return expression
end

# Pipeline
pipe label
  start with source
  filter when value modulo 2 equals 0
  map value times 2
  yield result_var
end

# Pattern match (catch error MANDATORY)
match expr
  when val1 yield statement
  when val2 yield statement
  catch error yield statement
end
```

## Reserved Words ‚Äî NEVER use as identifiers

```
intent let be set print skip read repeat while for each in pipe match
when catch error yield start with map filter transform end if then elif
else define taking return call passing list at put get plus minus times
divby modulo above below atleast atmost equals and or not true false value
```

## Critical Rules

1. Programs MUST start with `intent "description"`
2. Variables MUST be declared with `let` before mutation with `set`
3. All blocks end with `end` ‚Äî no braces, no indentation rules
4. `match` blocks MUST end with `catch error yield <statement>`
5. `value` is the pipe register ‚Äî NEVER use as a variable name
6. Functions have isolated scope ‚Äî can read outer vars but cannot mutate them
7. Type equality is strict ‚Äî `0 equals false` is `false`
8. `plus` with any string operand does string concatenation
9. `divby` and `modulo` throw on zero divisor

## Proof Manifest (Strict Mode)

When `--strict` is used, a `.lumo.proof.json` file must accompany the source:
```bash
./build/lumo --generate-proof-template program.lumo > program.lumo.proof.json
# Fill in safety proofs, then:
./build/lumo --strict program.lumo
```
